OL,6,FShe added: "He should have been safe
OL,7,Fbut instead he was subjected to
OL,8,Fprolonged and persistent abuse when he
OL,9,Fwas vulnerable, and supposedly in a
OL,10,Fplace of safety...J"He was not
OL,11,Fviolent, and he was not particularly
OL,12,Fagitated. He didn't need restraint."
OL,14,FThe court heard the victim was left in
OL,15,Fa cubicle alone with the three
OL,16,Fsecurity guards after being seen by
OL,17,Fmedical staff. Prosecutors told how
OL,18,Fthe trio proceeded to attack him for
OL,19,Fabout an hour, between 3am and 4am on
OL,20,F25 January 2023.
