OL,6,FHe said he 'loved to work' in his
OL,7,Fprevious job as an electrician, but
OL,8,Fleft his employment due to his
OL,9,Fstruggles with his mental health. He
OL,10,F'felt completely at the mercy of the
OL,11,Fsecurity guards' during the attack.JHe
OL,12,Fsaid: "The attack itself made me feel
OL,13,Freally vulnerable... I was out of it
OL,14,Fand don't remember a lot of what
OL,15,Fhappened but I do remember I couldn't
OL,16,Fdo anything to defend myself.J"After
OL,17,Fthe attack I was covered in bruises...
OL,18,FI also had my toe bent back. This
OL,19,Fcaused me agony for months, sometimes
OL,20,Fto the point where I couldn't walk.
OL,21,F"I'm also frightened of being in
OL,22,Fhospital since the attack. I feel I
OL,23,Fhave lost all trust and confidence in
OL,24,Fpeople of positions of trust and
OL,25,Fauthority.J"I think the people who did
OL,26,Fthis to me need to be dealt with
