OL,6,F"However, that night they abused the
OL,7,Ftrust placed in them when they caused
OL,8,Fdeliberate harm to a patient they
OL,9,Fshould have protected.J"The effect the
OL,10,Fassault had on the man should not be
OL,11,Funderestimated ` in his victim impact
OL,12,Fstatement, which was read to the court
OL,13,Fat today's sentence hearing, he said
OL,14,Fthe attack made him feel vulnerable,
OL,15,Fhe could do nothing to defend himself,
OL,16,Fhe is now frightened of attending
OL,17,Fhospitals and suffers panic attacks.
OL,18,F"Everyone has the right to go about
OL,19,Ftheir daily lives without fear of
OL,20,Fviolence. I hope that following the
OL,21,Fconclusion of this case the man can
OL,22,Fbegin to move on with his life."
